cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing and word embeddings. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) because it involves learning document-level mixtures of topic vectors. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) because it deals with document representations. It could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because it involves unsupervised learning, and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because it uses automatic differentiation frameworks.
